leaders must be over 21 years old and hold a valid 10-year British passport.</p>\n\n<p>A &lsquo;British national&rsquo; is someone who is a:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>British citizen </li>\n  <li>British overseas territories citizen</li>\n  <li>British overseas citizen</li>\n  <li>British subject</li>\n  <li>British national (overseas)</li>\n  <li>British protected person</li>\n</ul>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n<p>There’s no guarantee that collective passports will be accepted or rejected in any country  - wherever possible, young people should travel on their own passports.</p>\n</div>\n\n"},{"web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/collective-group-passports/countries-you-can-visit","slug":"countries-you-can-visit","order":2,"title":"Countries you can visit","body":"<p>The countries you can travel to or through on a collective passport are:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>Austria</li>\n  <li>Belgium</li>\n  <li>Denmark</li>\n  <li>France</li>\n  <li>Germany</li>\n  <li>Italy</li>\n  <li>Luxembourg</li>\n  <li>Malta</li>\n  <li>Netherlands</li>\n  <li>Norway</li>\n  <li>Poland</li>\n  <li>Romania</li>\n  <li>Slovenia</li>\n  <li>Spain</li>\n  <li>Sweden</li>\n  <li>Switzerland</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>Visas</h2>\n\n<p>The rules about visas and collective passports vary by country - <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.fco.gov.uk/en/travel-and-living-abroad/foreign-embassies-in-uk/\" title=\"find foreign embassies in the UK\">contact the country&rsquo;s embassy or consulate in the UK</a> for more information. </p>\n"},{"web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/collective-group-passports/how-to-apply","slug":"how-to-apply","order":3,"title":"How to apply","body":"<p>Follow these steps to apply for a collective passport:</p>\n\n<ol class=\"steps\">\n<li><p>Download the <a href=\"http://www.homeoffice.gov.uk/publications/agencies-public-bodies/ips/general-ips-publications/passports/collective-passport-application?view=Binary\" title=\"application form (DOC, 915KB)\" rel=\"external\">applicatio