alable plastic bag, which holds no more than a litre and measures approximately 20cm x 20cm</li>\n  <li>contents must fit comfortably inside the bag so it can be sealed</li>\n  <li>the bag must not be knotted or tied at the top</li>\n  <li>it is limited to 1 plastic bag per person</li>\n  <li>you must show the bag at the airport security point</li>\n</ul>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n<p>Containers larger than 100ml (except essential medicines) will not be allowed through the security point even if they are only part full.</p>\n</div>\n\n<p>Liquids include:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>all drinks, including water, soup and syrups</li>\n  <li>cosmetics and toiletries, including creams, lotions, oils, perfumes, mascara and lipsticks</li>\n  <li>sprays, including shaving foam, hairspray and spray deodorants</li>\n  <li>pastes, including toothpaste</li>\n  <li>gels, including hair and shower gel</li>\n  <li>contact lens solution</li>\n  <li>any other solutions and items of similar consistency</li>\n</ul>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice help-notice\">\n<p>Airport security staff may confiscate anything they consider dangerous - even if it’s normally allowed in hand luggage.</p>\n</div>\n\n<h2>Lighters</h2>\n<p>You can only carry 1 lighter on board and it should be put it inside a plastic bag for liquids. You must keep the lighter with you throughout the flight. You can&rsquo;t:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>place it in your hold luggage  </li>\n  <li>return it to your hand luggage after screening</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>Download the Civil Aviation Authority&rsquo;s (CAA&rsquo;s) guide for full details of what you can carry in your baggage.</p>\n\n<div class=\"form-download\">\n<p><a href=\"http://www.caa.co.uk/docs/1219/srg_dgo_WhatCanICarry20120321.pdf\" title=\"Download 'CAA - what can I carry?' (PDF, 93KB)\">Download ‘CAA - what can I carry?’ (PDF, 93KB)</a></p>\n</div>\n"},{"web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/hand-luggage-restrictions/baby-food-and-baby-milk","slug":"baby-food