</h2>\n\n<p>If you&rsquo;re in the UK, you can:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li><a rel=\"external\" href=\"https://passports.ips.gov.uk\" title=\"Online passport application form\">fill in the form online</a> - the Identity and Passport Service (<abbr title=\"Identity and Passport Service\">IPS</abbr>) will post it back to you to check and sign</li>\n  <li>get one from a Post Office that offers the <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.postoffice.co.uk/branch-finder\" title=\"Post Office branch finder\">Check &amp; Send service</a></li>\n  <li>call the Passport Adviceline and get them to post you one</li>\n</ul>\n\n<div class=\"contact\">\n<p><strong>Passport Adviceline</strong>  </p>\n\n<p><strong>Telephone</strong> 0300 222 0000<br />\n<strong>Textphone</strong> 0300 222 0222  <br />\n<strong>Text Relay</strong> 18001 0300 222 0000<br />\nMonday to Friday, 8am to 8pm  <br />\nSaturday, Sunday and public holidays, 9am to 5:30pm</p>\n</div>\n\n<p>If you&rsquo;re outside the UK, you must apply to the <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.fco.gov.uk/en/travel-and-living-abroad/passports1/\" title=\"Renewing a passport when overseas\">Foreign and Commonwealth Office.</a></p>\n\n<h3>Help filling in the form</h3>\n\n<p>The form comes with notes to help you fill it in. You can download a copy of the notes.</p>\n\n<div class=\"form-download\">\n<p><a href=\"http://www.direct.gov.uk/prod_consum_dg/groups/dg_digitalassets/@dg/@en/@travel/documents/digitalasset/dg_184487.pdf\" title=\"Download 'Guidance notes - Applying for a passport' (PDF, 495KB)\" rel=\"external\">Download ‘Guidance notes - Applying for a passport’ (PDF, 495KB)</a></p>\n</div>\n\n<h2>Photos</h2>\n\n<p>You must include 2 identical new photos of yourself. </p>\n\n<p><a href=\"/photos-for-passports\" title=\"Passport photos\">Follow the rules about passport photos</a> or your application may be rejected.</p>\n\n<h2>Countersignatories</h2>\n\n<p>You must get your application form and 1 of your photos signed by someone else to prove your identity if either:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>you can&rsquo;t be recognised from the photo in your existing passport </li>\n  <li>you&rsquo;re replacing a damaged passport</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>Check <a href=\"/who-can-sign-passport-driving-licence-applications\" title=\"Who can sign passport applications and photos\">who can countersign your application and photo</a> and what they have to do. </p>\n\n<h2>Send your application</h2>\n\n<p>You can either:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>use the Post Office <a href=\"/how-the-post-office-check-and-send-service-works\" title=\"Check &amp; Send service\">Check &amp; Send service</a></li>\n  <li>post your application using the pre-printed envelope that comes with the form and include your existing passport, photos and supporting documents. </li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>You can pay by debit or credit card (by completing the form in the application pack) or make a cheque payable to &lsquo;Identity and Passport Service&rsquo;.</p>\n\n<h2>What happens next</h2>\n\n<p>The <abbr title=\"Identity and Passport Service\">IPS</abbr> will check your application. Your new passport will be sent to your home address. You may have to sign for it.</p>\n\n<p>If you want to check your application&rsquo;s progress, call the Passport Adviceline - you can do this <strong>2 weeks</strong> after you&rsquo;ve made your application. </p>\n\n<p>When you call, you need either:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>the barcode number from your application form</li>\n  <li>the number on your receipt if you used Check &amp; Send or applied at a Passport Customer Service Centre</li>\n</ul>\n\n<div class=\"contact\">\n<p><strong>Passport Adviceline</strong>  </p>\n\n<p><strong>Telephone:</strong> 0300 222 0000<br />\n<strong>Textphone:</strong> 0300 222 0222  <br />\n<strong>Text Relay:</strong> 18001 0300 222 0000<br />\nMonday to Friday, 8am to 8pm  <br />\nSaturday, Sunday and public holidays, 9am to 5:30pm</p>\n</div>\n\n","alternative_title":""},"updated_at":"2012-11-08T14:37:42+00:00",