/www.defra.gov.uk/wildlife-pets/pets/travel/pets/routes/\" title=\"Defra list of PETS routes and transport companies\"><abbr title=\"Pet Travel Scheme\">PETS</abbr>-approved sea, air or rail route.</a></p>\n\n<p>Most major ferry companies, airlines and rail operators are approved.</p>\n\n<h2>When you return to the UK</h2>\n\n<p>Your pet&rsquo;s microchip will be scanned and its passport inspected.</p>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice help-notice\">\n<p>If you don’t have the correct paperwork or your pet hasn’t been prepared properly, it will be put into quarantine or sent back to the country it travelled from.</p>\n</div>\n\n<h2>Travelling with multiple animals</h2>\n\n<p>There are <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.defra.gov.uk/wildlife-pets/pets/travel/pets/pet-owners\" title=\"extra rules\">extra rules</a> if you&rsquo;re travelling with more than 5 cats, dogs or ferrets.</p>\n\n<h2>Other types of animal</h2>\n\n<p>There are different rules covering the movement of <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.defra.gov.uk/wildlife-pets/pets/travel/pets/other-animals\" title=\"other types of pets\">other types of pets.</a></p>\n\n"},{"web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/take-pet-abroad/unlisted-countries","slug":"unlisted-countries","order":2,"title":"Unlisted countries","body":"<p>Cats, dogs and ferrets travelling to unlisted countries must also:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>have a blood sample taken by a vet at least 30 days after it was vaccinated (the date of vaccination counts as day 0 and not day 1)</li>\n  <li>have passed the blood test (the vet will give you a compliance certificate) </li>\n  <li>wait 3 calendar months from the date the blood sample was taken before re-entering the UK</li>\n</ul>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n<p>The 3-month waiting period doesn’t apply if your pet was vaccinated and blood tested in the EU and issued with an EU pet passport before travelling to an unlisted country.</p>\n</div>\n\n<h2>Other rules for unlisted countries</h2